<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-727-012  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 727 012.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Weekly  Sept 14 1989 n1181 p26(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Unclear, irrelevant and too technical.... (computer documentation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mehta, Angeli.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Twenty percent of end-users never bother referring todocumentation, depending on their data processing department tohelp instead of dealing with the frustrations of manuals that areunclear, too technical, badly indexed, and lacking in examples.andO;Programmers hate to write documentation and as a result UnitedKingdom companies waste money on useless system documentation.andO;Companies do not properly plan for documentation, often waitinguntil a month before the program is scheduled to ship beforestarting on the manuals.andP;  Decent documentation takes three to sixmonths.andP;  The traditional approach, with programmers or technicalwriters writing the documentation, is inadequate.andP;  The writersneed the ability to communicate with the user and an understandingof the user's needs.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     DocumentationTechnical WritingNew TechniqueSupport ServicesUser Behavior.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>